        cart_table.grant_read_write_data(payment_processor)
        orders_table.grant_read_data(checkout_status_function)

        # Amazon SQS permissions for message flow
        inventory_queue.grant_send_messages(checkout_handler)
        inventory_queue.grant_consume_messages(inventory_processor)
        payment_queue.grant_send_messages(inventory_processor)
        payment_queue.grant_consume_messages(payment_processor)
        fulfillment_queue.grant_send_messages(payment_processor)
        fulfillment_queue.grant_consume_messages(fulfillment_processor)

        # Idempotency table access for all functions
        idempotency_table.grant_read_write_data(cart_handler)
        idempotency_table.grant_read_write_data(checkout_handler)
        idempotency_table.grant_read_write_data(inventory_processor)
        idempotency_table.grant_read_write_data(payment_processor)
        idempotency_table.grant_read_write_data(fulfillment_processor)

        # Amazon EventBridge permissions for event publishing
        ecommerce_bus.grant_put_events_to(cart_handler)

Event-Driven Processing Pipeline
Amazon EventBridge rules route events by pattern matching. Amazon SQS event sources trigger processors with batch_size=1. AWS IAM permissions follow least privilege. Idempotency table prevents duplicate processing. Fully serverless with automatic scaling.
Understanding the Event Flow
Complete Architecture Flow: Amazon API Gateway → Amazon EventBridge → AWS Lambda → Amazon SQS → Processors

This event-driven architecture enables your e-commerce system to handle orders asynchronously while providing immediate user feedback. Each stage serves a specific purpose in creating a scalable, reliable order processing system.

Stage	Technology	Benefit	Role in E-Commerce
API Response	Amazon EventBridge	Immediate (~50ms)	Customer gets instant checkout confirmation
Event Routing	AWS Lambda Handlers	Smart processing	Business logic without blocking APIs
Reliable Queuing	Amazon SQS Triggers	Guaranteed delivery	Orders never lost, automatic retries
Observability	Amazon CloudWatch	Full visibility	Monitor order completion rates
